Reasoning: The paper deals with algorithmic problems on graphs, such as finding shortest cycles, computing diameter and radius, and finding minimum weight perfect matchings. These are typical topics in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper uses matrix multiplication and determinant algorithms, which are also relevant to cs.NA and cs.CC.
